XJXzpUzQNlA5pEf_Rk8l2U=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing JavaAdapter details**\\n\\nI’m considering if `JavaAdapter.convertResult` for integers actually returns a Java Integer. It looks like there’s a need to join calls to `toString`. I’m also thinking about a serialization script that starts with creating a new `JavaAdapter`. I need to make sure to define the functions for describing and greeting properly, then serialize that through `ScriptableOutputStream`, which does not include standard features. I should also interpret the source functions and consider optimization levels. I'll explore the `try-with-resources` for closing the `ScriptableOutputStream`.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_9Dmqk3RqKmx8vzG14ZD9lKlz|fc_05d6d4edd3301d4e0169f79793ac2c8196b61579dd18746ba3", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/src/test/java/org_mozilla/rhino/JavaAdapterTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_mozilla.rhino;\n\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertEquals;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertInstanceOf;\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\n\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.mozilla.javascript.Context;\nimport org.mozilla.javascript.ContextFactory;\nimport org.mozilla.javascript.Scriptable;\nimport org.mozilla.javascript.Wrapper;\nimport org.mozilla.javascript.serialize.ScriptableInputStream;\nimport org.mozilla.javascript.serialize.ScriptableOutputStream;\n\npublic class JavaAdapterTest {\n    public interface NamedJob {\n        String describe(String value);\n\n        int inherited();\n    }\n\n    public static class AdapterBase {\n        public AdapterBase() {\n        }\n\n        public AdapterBase(String ignored) {\n        }\n\n        public int inherited() {\n            return 7;\n        }\n\n        public String greet(String name) {\n            return \"base:\" + name;\n        }\n\n        protected String protectedHook() {\n            return \"protected\";\n        }\n\n        public final String finalMethod() {\n            return \"final\";\n        }\n\n        public static String staticMethod() {\n            return \"static\";\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    public void createsAdapterFromJavaScriptImplementation() {\n        try {\n            assertAdapterCreation();\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            rethrowUnlessUnsupportedDynamicClassLoading(error);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    public void serializesAndDeserializesAdapterWrapper() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            assertAdapterSerialization();\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            rethrowUnlessUnsupportedDynamicClassLoading(error);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private void assertAdapterCreation() {\n        Context cx = ContextFactory.getGlobal().enterContext();\n        try {\n            cx.setOptimizationLevel(-1);\n            Scriptable scope = cx.initStandardObjects();\n            Object result = cx.evaluateString(scope, adapterCreationScript(), \"adapterCreation\", 1, null);\n\n            assertEquals(\"js:item|7|hello Bob|base:Bob\", Context.toString(result));\n        } finally {\n            Context.exit();\n        }\n    }\n\n    private void assertAdapterSerialization() throws Exception {\n        Context cx = ContextFactory.getGlobal().enterContext();\n        try {\n            cx.setOptimizationLevel(-1);\n            Scriptable scope = cx.initStandardObjects();\n            Object adapter = cx.evaluateString(scope, serializableAdapterScript(), \"serializableAdapter\", 1, null);\n\n            ByteArrayOutputStream serialized = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n            try (ScriptableOutputStream output = new ScriptableOutputStream(serialized, scope)) {\n                output.writeObject(adapter);\n            }\n\n            Object restored;\n            try (ScriptableInputStream input = new ScriptableInputStream(\n                    new ByteArrayInputStream(serialized.toByteArray()), scope)) {\n                restored = input.readObject();\n            }\n\n            Wrapper wrapper = assertInstanceOf(Wrapper.class, restored);\n            Object unwrapped = wrapper.unwrap();\n            NamedJob job = assertInstanceOf(NamedJob.class, unwrapped);\n            AdapterBase base = assertInstanceOf(AdapterBase.class, unwrapped);\n\n            assertEquals(\"stored:value\", job.describe(\"value\"));\n            assertEquals(7, job.inherited());\n            assertEquals(\"stored-greet:Ann\", base.greet(\"Ann\"));\n        } finally {\n            Context.exit();\n        }\n    }\n\n    private String adapterCreationScript() {\n        return \"\"\"\n                var adapter = new JavaAdapter(Packages.%s, Packages.%s, {\n                  describe: function(value) {\n                    return 'js:' + value;\n                  },\n                  greet: function(name) {\n                    return 'hello ' + name;\n                  }\n                });\n                [\n                  adapter.describe('item'),\n                  adapter.inherited(),\n                  adapter.greet('Bob'),\n                  adapter.super$greet('Bob')\n                ].join('|');\n                \"\"\".formatted(AdapterBase.class.getName(), NamedJob.class.getName());\n    }\n\n    private String serializableAdapterScript() {\n        return \"\"\"\n                new JavaAdapter(Packages.%s, Packages.%s, {\n                  describe: function(value) {\n                    return 'stored:' + value;\n                  },\n                  greet: function(name) {\n                    return 'stored-greet:' + name;\n                  }\n                });\n                \"\"\".formatted(AdapterBase.class.getName(), NamedJob.class.getName());\n    }\n\n    private void rethrowUnlessUnsupportedDynamicClassLoading(Error error) {\n        if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n            throw error;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 692, "output": 2162, "cacheRead": 38912, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 41766, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777833862850, "responseId": "resp_05d6d4edd3301d4e0169f7978754e88196961290217348ac66"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_9Dmqk3RqKmx8vzG14ZD9lKlz|fc_05d6d4edd3301d4e0169f79793ac2c8196b61579dd18746ba3", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 5160 bytes to tests/src/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/src/test/java/org_mozilla/rhino/JavaAdapterTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777833882789}]}
